<h1>BlazorECharts Samples</h1>

<p>
    Welcome to the <strong>BlazorECharts</strong> sample application. This project demonstrates how to use
    the BlazorECharts library to integrate Apache ECharts into a Blazor WebAssembly application.
</p>

<h2>What is BlazorECharts?</h2>
<p>
    BlazorECharts is a Blazor component library that wraps
    <a href="https://echarts.apache.org/" target="_blank">Apache ECharts</a>,
    a powerful open-source charting and visualization library. It provides a simple
    <code>&lt;EChart&gt;</code> component that you can configure with strongly-typed C# models
    or anonymous objects.
</p>

<h2>Samples Overview</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Line Chart</strong> - Multiple line series with smooth curves and data points.</li>
    <li><strong>Bar Chart</strong> - Grouped and stacked bar charts with multiple series.</li>
    <li><strong>Pie Chart</strong> - Pie chart with labels and emphasis effects.</li>
    <li><strong>Sankey Diagram</strong> - Flow diagram showing relationships between nodes.</li>
    <li><strong>Dynamic Update</strong> - Timer-based live data updates every 2 seconds.</li>
    <li><strong>Click Events</strong> - Handling click events on chart data points.</li>
    <li><strong>Typed Model</strong> - Building chart configuration using strongly-typed C# models.</li>
    <li><strong>Dark Theme</strong> - Toggling between light and dark ECharts themes.</li>
    <li><strong>Resizable Chart</strong> - Chart inside a resizable container using CSS flexbox.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Getting Started</h2>
<p>
    Use the navigation menu on the left to explore each example. Every page is self-contained
    with both the rendered chart and a description of the approach used.
</p>
